    <br/>

    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li>As an Administrator, I want a dedicated logging structure so that I can track user login activity and browser types as required by the V2 project specifications.</li>
	<li><b>Technical Scope:</b>
	<ul>
		<li>Design and deploy the <tt>UserActivityLogs</tt> table.</li>
		<li><b>Columns:</b> <tt>Id</tt> (UUID), <tt>UserId</tt> (FK), <tt>Action</tt> (e.g., 'LOGIN_SUCCESS'), <tt>IPAddress</tt>, <tt>UserAgent</tt> (Text), <tt>CreatedAt</tt> (Timestamp).</li>
		<li><b>Optimization:</b> Create a non-clustered index on <tt>UserId</tt> and <tt>CreatedAt</tt> to optimize for the "Last Login" lookup query used in <b><span class="error">&#91;GREEN-1.3&#93;</span></b>.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b>
	<ul>
		<li>The table successfully logs a dummy entry via a manual SQL insert.</li>
		<li>The Foreign Key to the <tt>Users</tt> table is configured with <tt>ON DELETE SET NULL</tt> to preserve logs even if a user account is deleted (for audit compliance).</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

<hr class='fullcontent'><br /><br style='page-break-before:always;'/><br />
