    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li>As a System Owner, I want the system to be pre-populated with Greenwich-specific roles and faculties so that we can begin testing role-based access immediately.</li>
	<li><b>Technical Scope:</b>
	<ul>
		<li>Create a SQL seeding script that populates the static lookup tables.</li>
		<li><b>Faculties:</b> Insert "Business", "IT", "Creative Arts", "Engineering", etc.</li>
		<li><b>Roles:</b> Insert "Administrator", "Marketing Manager", "Marketing Coordinator", "Student", and "Guest".</li>
		<li><b>Test Data:</b> Create one test user per role with a known hashed password (provided by Min Khant).</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b>
	<ul>
		<li>Running the seed script results in zero errors.</li>
		<li>A <tt>SELECT</tt> query confirms the presence of all 5 roles and all faculties.</li>
		<li>Verification that a <tt>User</tt> can be successfully mapped to a <tt>Faculty</tt> and a <tt>Role</tt>.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

