    <br/>

    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li><b>User Story:</b> As a Developer, I want a signed JWT token containing user role and faculty claims so that the frontend and API can enforce security boundaries without repetitive DB lookups.</li>
	<li><b>Technical Scope:</b>
	<ul>
		<li>Configure <tt>Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer</tt> in <tt>Program.cs</tt>.</li>
		<li>Implement a <tt>JwtProvider</tt> to generate tokens with the following claims:
		<ul>
			<li><tt>sub</tt>: Unique User ID (UUID).</li>
			<li><tt>role</tt>: User Role (e.g., "Student", "MarketingCoordinator").</li>
			<li><tt>faculty_id</tt>: The ID of the faculty the user belongs to.</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Configure a Global Authorization Policy that requires a valid Bearer token for all <tt><span class="error">&#91;Authorize&#93;</span></tt> attributes.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b>
	<ul>
		<li>The JWT is signed using <tt>SymmetricSecurityKey</tt> with <tt>HMACSHA256</tt>.</li>
		<li>The token contains an <tt>exp</tt> (expiration) claim set to 8 hours.</li>
		<li>Middleware successfully returns $403\text
{ Forbidden}
<p>$ if a user with the "Student" role attempts to access an endpoint decorated with <tt><span class="error">&#91;Authorize(Roles = &quot;Admin&quot;)&#93;</span></tt>.</p></li>
		<li>The token is retrievable via a standard <tt>Bearer</tt> header in Postman.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

